EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to natural resources; prohibiting the sale, offer for
sale or distribution for sale of water in certain disposable
plastic bottles within any community which abuts the
Lake Tahoe Watershed; requiring, under certain
circumstances, the local board of health or health
department to issue administrative fines for such a
violation; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law establishes certain prohibitions relating to water pollution in Lake
2 Tahoe and within the Lake Tahoe Watershed. (NRS 445A.170-445A.190) Section
3 1 of this bill prohibits a person from selling, offering for sale or distributing for sale
4 water in a disposable plastic bottle that has a capacity of not more than 4 liters in
5 any community which abuts the Lake Tahoe Watershed. Section 1 requires the
6 local board of health or health department to enforce this prohibition. Section 1
7 further requires the local board of health or health department to: (1) for a first
8 violation of section 1 within 1 year, issue a warning; (2) for a second violation
9 within 1 year, impose an administrative fine of not more than $100; (3) for a third
10 violation within 1 year, impose an administrative fine of not more than $200; and
11 (4) for a fourth or subsequent violation within 1 year impose an administrative fine
12 of not more than $500.
