THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 445A of NRS is hereby amended by
2 adding thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. A person shall not sell, offer to sell or distribute for sale
4 water in a disposable plastic bottle that has a capacity of not more
5 than 4 liters in any community that abuts the Lake Tahoe
6 Watershed.
7 2. The local board of health or health department with
8 jurisdiction in the county, city or health district shall enforce the
9 provisions of this section. For any violation of the provisions of
10 this section, the local board of health or health department, as
11 applicable, shall:
12 (a) For a first violation within 1 year, issue a warning to the
13 person who is in violation of this section.
14 (b) For a second violation within 1 year, impose a fine of not
15 more than $100.
16 (c) For a third violation within 1 year, impose a fine of not
17 more than $200.
18 (d) For a fourth or subsequent violation within 1 year, impose
19 a fine of not more than $500.
20 3. As used in this section:
21 (a) “Disposable plastic bottle” means a single-use or
22 disposable item that is made of plastic and used for bottling,
23 packaging, serving, consuming or transporting water.
24 (b) “Local board of health” means a county board of health,
25 city board of health or district board of health.
26 (c) “Plastic” means a synthetic or semisynthetic material
27 chemically synthesized by the polymerization of organic
28 substances that can be molded and shaped into rigid and flexible
29 forms.
30 Sec. 2. (Deleted by amendment.)
31 Sec. 3. (Deleted by amendment.)
32 Sec. 4. The provisions of NRS 354.599 do not apply to any
33 additional expenses of a local government that are related to the
34 provisions of this act.
35 Sec. 5. This act becomes effective on January 1, 2026.
